article.headline: Norfolk St. 82, N. Carolina A&amp,T 76
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Michael Deloach scored 24 points and Tony Murphy added 20 to lead Norfolk State to an 82-76 win over North Carolina A&T on Saturday. It was a tight game, with the Spartans (2-4, 1-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) never ahead by more than seven points. They led 37-36 at the half. A layup by Deloach with 7:03 left on the clock tied the teams at 64. He sunk a 3-pointer a minute later, giving the Spartans the lead for good and snapping his team's four-game losing streak. Steven Rush led the Aggies (4-4, 0-1) in scoring with 16 points, and Thomas Coleman had 12 points and nine rebounds. The Spartans shot 50 percent from the field to the Aggies' 40.7 percent, but the Aggies had 41 rebounds to Norfolk's 28.
